records.addlTxt:
The State files an Amended Information which charges one count of possess Amphetamine, contrary to Section 961.41(3g)(d) and one count possess paraphernalia, contrary to section 961.573(1).
GUILTY pleas entered to both counts in the Amended Information. Convicted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for eighteen (18) months.
Conditions of probation:
1) AODA assessment and follow through;
2) Assessment, treatment, counseling and deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
3) Maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination;
4) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
5) Spend thirty (30) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, on count 1 only, stayed and to be imposed at the agents discretion and upon order of the court;
6) Provide DNA sample;
7) Pay court costs;
8) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Minutes.
